85%, ending the session at 61.40.\n\nThe leaders of the fall were shares of JetAI Inc (NASDAQ:JTAI), which declined in price by 39.16%, closing at 1.60. Shares of Milestone Pharmaceuticals Inc (NASDAQ:MIST) lost 30.90% and ended the session at 1.99. MicroAlgo Inc (NASDAQ:MLGO) quotes decreased in price by 30.67% to 1.13.\n\nOn the New York Stock Exchange, the number of securities that rose in price (2,126) exceeded the number of those that closed in the red (752), and the quotes of 73 shares remained virtually unchanged. On the NASDAQ stock exchange, the securities of 2,340 companies rose in price, 1,113 declined, and 99 remained at the level of the previous close.\n\nIntel Corporation (NASDAQ:INTC) stock prices rose to a 52-week high, rising by 5.21%, 2.50 p., and ended trading at 50.50. Intel Corporation (NASDAQ:INTC) stock prices rose to a 52-week high, rising by 5.21%, 2.50 p., and ended trading at 50.50. Caterpillar Inc (NYSE:CAT) stock prices rose to a historic high, rising by 1.82%, 5.27 p., and ended trading at 295.63. The share prices of Milestone Pharmaceuticals Inc (NASDAQ:MIST) fell to a 3-year low, falling by 30.90%, 0.89 p., and ended trading at 1.99. The stock prices of RayzeBio Inc (NASDAQ:RYZB) rose to a historic high, rising by 100.85%, 30.83 p., and ended trading at 61.40. MicroAlgo Inc (NASDAQ:MLGO) stock prices fell to a historic low, falling by 30.67%, 0.50 p., and ended trading at 1.13.\n\nThe CBOE Volatility Index, which is formed based on the performance of options trading on the S&P 500, fell 0.31% to 12.99.\n\nGold futures for February delivery added 0.46%, or 9.50, to reach $2.00 per troy ounce. As for other commodities, prices for WTI crude futures for February delivery rose by 2.30%, or 1.69, to $75.25 per barrel. Brent crude futures for March delivery rose 2.20%, or 1.73, to $80.53 per barrel.\n\nMeanwhile, on the Forex market, the EUR/USD pair did not change significantly by 0.32% to 1.10, and the USD/JPY quotes increased by 0.06%, reaching 142.43.\n\nFutures for the USD index fell 0.22% to 101.11.",
